{{Orphan|date=May 2011}}

'''Drygalski Basin''' ({{coord|74|50|S|166|30|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea basin named as such by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] (ACUF) in April 1980, in association with [[Drygalski Ice Tongue]]. The name was changed to "Von Drygalski" in November 1995, in agreement with the [[General Bathymetric Chart of the Oceans]] Sub-Committee on Undersea Feature Names, but was changed back to Drygalski Basin by ACUF in June 2003.<ref name=gnis/>

