The '''Tagaytay–Calamba Road''' is a  two-to-four lane,  secondary and tertiary road in [[Laguna (province)|Laguna]] and [[Cavite]], [[Philippines]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2015RBI/2015%20DPWH%20Road%20Data/Road%20Data%202015/laguna_2nd.htm|title=Laguna 2nd|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2015RBI/2015%20DPWH%20Road%20Data/Road%20Data%202015/cavite_sub.htm|title=Cavite 2nd|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref> It connects the city of [[Calamba, Laguna|Calamba]] in [[Laguna (province)|Laguna]] and the city of [[Tagaytay]] in [[Cavite]].

The segment of road in Tagaytay is a component of '''National Route 421''' ('''N421''') of the [[Philippine highway network]], while the rest of the road remains unnumbered.

