==Surviving models==
A scale model [[Poluwat]] ''wa'' collected by David Lewis and Barry Lewis, father and son, in 1969 is held by the [[Australian National Maritime Museum]] at [[Darling Harbour]], [[Sydney]], Australia.{{efn-ua|An aggregation of scale model canoes at the museum including the following: a [[Poluwat]] ''wa'' – [[Caroline Islands]]; [[Kapingamarangi canoe|''Kapingamarangi'' canoe]] – [[Federated States of Micronesia]]; ''[[Tepukei|Te Puke]]'' – [[Solomon Islands]]; [[Kiribati]] – ''Nikunau''; and ''[[Ninigo]]'' – [[Papua New Guinea]]. A fifth model collected in 1976 is a [[Hawaiian canoe]].<ref name="Maritime">{{cite web |url=https://anmm.wordpress.com/tag/poluwot-wa/ |title=Navigating without instruments |publisher=[[Australian National Maritime Museum]] |date=December 4, 2009 |author=stephengapps |accessdate=January 7, 2015}}</ref>
These all were collected by David Lewis and Barry Lewis, father and son, incidental to research of Indigenous [[navigation]] practices and [[Travel|ocean voyaging]], which sought understanding of long traverses of parts of across the Pacific Ocean, the so-called [[Polynesian navigation]], without the aid of modern [[navigational instrument|navigational tools]].<ref name="Maritime"/>}} A further, damaged, small scale model is also in Sydney at the [[Powerhouse Museum]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://from.ph/211553 |title=Ship model,sailing canoe Caroline islands |accessdate=10 January 2015 |publisher=Powerhouse Museum, Australia}}</ref>

Two additional models of ''wa'' craft from [[Yap]], made before 1909, are held at the [[Ethnological Museum of Berlin]] in Germany.<ref name="berlin-model1">{{cite web|url=http://www.smb-digital.de/eMuseumPlus?service=ExternalInterface&module=collection&objectId=1360701&viewType=detailView |title=Model #1, Modell eines Auslegerbootes Modell eines Auslegerbootes, Arno Senfft (28.3.1864 &ndash; 14.2.1909), Sammler |first1=Heinz-Günther |last1=Malenz|publisher= [[Ethnological Museum of Berlin]] |accessdate=January 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name="berlin-model2">{{cite web|url=http://www.smb-digital.de/eMuseumPlus?service=ExternalInterface&module=collection&objectId=1360699&viewType=detailView|title=Model #2  Modell eines Auslegerbootes Arno Senfft (28.3.1864 &ndash; 14.2.1909), Sammler |first1=Claudia |last1=Obrocki|publisher=[[Ethnological Museum of Berlin]] |accessdate=January 12, 2015}}</ref>

